Hungary Mortgage-Relief Plan Near Conclusion, Portfolio Reports

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-03-25T08:15:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/hungary-mortgage-relief-plan-near-conclusion-portfolio-reports.html
Hungary’s government and commercial
banks are close to agreement on a mortgage-relief plan aimed at
helping distressed borrowers, news portal  Portfolio.hu  reported,
citing a bank executive.  The plan won’t include fixing the forint’s exchange rate on
foreign-currency mortgages, Portfolio said, citing Daniel Gyuris, the chief executive officer of OTP Jelzalogbank Zrt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  